In a Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) model, the process of deciding which expert handles which token is managed by a specialized component called the **Gating Network** (also known as the **Router**).

Instead of passing every token through every neural network layer, the router acts as a "traffic controller" that directs each token to a small subset of specialized "experts."

Here is the step-by-step breakdown of how this decision-making process works:

---

